## Summary

Standardize PhenoCompose README with DAG-compliant work-state header and fix broken CI badges that referenced non-existent workflows.

## Context

As part of DAG unit A9 in the compute/infra epic_A hygiene sweep, the README needed:
- A standardized work-state header following the phenotype-infra pattern (epic status, DAG phase, progress indicator)
- CI badges that actually point to existing workflows instead of the non-existent `quality-gate.yml`

## Changes

- **Work-state header**: Replaced stale `Work State: docs/readme-m2` line with EPIC_A / DAG phase A9 pattern matching phenotype-infra's README style
- **Rust CI badge**: Added inline Rust CI badge at the top for immediate build status visibility
- **Build badge**: Fixed `quality-gate.yml` → `rust-ci.yml` with updated workflow URL
- **CI badge**: Fixed `quality-gate.yml` → `ci.yml` (renamed from "Quality Gate" to "CI")

## Testing

Verify badges render correctly at:
- [Rust CI](https://github.com/KooshaPari/PhenoCompose/actions/workflows/rust-ci.yml)
- [CI](https://github.com/KooshaPari/PhenoCompose/actions/workflows/ci.yml)

View the rendered README on the branch to confirm the work-state header displays correctly.
